The paper discusses recent advances in algorithms for numerical linear algebra, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the numerical solution of linear algebra problems. The technique of linear sketching, which is the focus of the paper, is a method for compressing matrices to accelerate the solution of these problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), which deals with the development and analysis of numerical algorithms for solving mathematical problems. 

The paper also discusses applications of sketching to problems such as low rank approximation and graph sparsification, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of random matrices in sketching also has connections to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
